{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ecf4dcb4-2198-4ec5-bd42-593f781a15dc","content":"\n\nHere's a quick overview:\n\n**Templates:**\n- **ASP.NET Core Web API** (`dotnet new webapi`) — most popular for .NET\n- **Express.js** (`express-generator`) — Node.js\n- **FastAPI** / **Django REST Framework** — Python\n- **Spring Boot** — Java\n\n**Common Authentication Options (ASP.NET Core as example):**\n| Option | Use Case |\n|---|---|\n| **JWT Bearer** | SPAs, mobile apps, microservices |\n| **OAuth2 / OpenID Connect** | Third-party login (Google, GitHub, etc.) |\n| **Cookie-based** | Traditional server-rendered apps |\n| **API Keys** | Simple service-to-service auth |\n| **Windows/Negotiate** | Intranet/enterprise apps |\n| **Identity Platform** (Azure AD / Entra ID) | Microsoft ecosystem |\n\n**Quick start with .NET:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual   # Identity + JWT\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg    # Azure AD\ndotnet new webapi --auth None         # Add your own later\n```\n\nWant me to scaffold a specific project? If so, let me know your preferred language/framework and auth type.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d3a6354d-ce69-4e87-b8c2-aa15b2ff44a4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward informational question I can answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":344},"id":"ab2c4466-6b2b-4e57-86b2-a769298e7f06","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:56:36.323Z","parentId":"fd90b834-b659-4644-b879-81d81bbb15ef"}
